      &lt;stopSequences&gt;sadsadsad&lt;/stopSequences&gt;
      &lt;candidateCount&gt;1&lt;/candidateCount&gt;
      &lt;maxOutputTokens&gt;50000&lt;/maxOutputTokens&gt;
      &lt;temperature&gt;0.5&lt;/temperature&gt;
      &lt;topP&gt;0.5&lt;/topP&gt;
      &lt;topK&gt;2&lt;/topK&gt;
&lt;/generationConfig&gt;</expression>
                  </operation>
                  <operation source="formula" to="temp.Tmp_Request">
                     <expression language="XQuery">&lt;Generate_Content_Request&gt;
   &lt;contents&gt;
      &lt;parts&gt;
         &lt;text&gt;You are an Informatica Support Freature Request Agent. You are specialized in creating Jira tickets from received emails. Format all this information clearly and concisely into a Jira ticket template with the following key details and using this exact format:
Summary:
(a short, clear headline based on the email subject)

Description:
(a detailed explanation based on the email body). 
The Feature Request is an e-mail from a customer, it will be provided to you in format: E-Mail Subject: given subject E-Mail Body: given body The provided query is: E-Mail Subject: {$temp.Tmp_Email_Subject }   E-Mail Body: {$temp.Tmp_Email_Body  }.Ensure that the response is only summary and description without any comments. &lt;/text&gt;
      &lt;/parts&gt;
      &lt;role&gt;user&lt;/role&gt;
   &lt;/contents&gt;
 &lt;generationConfig&gt;
      &lt;stopSequences&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/stopSequences }&lt;/stopSequences&gt;
      &lt;candidateCount&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/candidateCount }&lt;/candidateCount&gt;
      &lt;maxOutputTokens&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/maxOutputTokens  }&lt;/maxOutputTokens&gt;
      &lt;temperature&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/temperature }&lt;/temperature&gt;
      &lt;topP&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/topP  }&lt;/topP&gt;
      &lt;topK&gt;{$temp.Tmp_Prompt_Configuration[1]/topK  }&lt;/topK&gt;
   &lt;/generationConfig&gt;
&lt;/Generate_Content_Request&gt;
</expression>
                  </operation>
